WITH new_values (employee_id, name, position, department) AS (VALUES
    (1, 'John Doe', 'Manager', 'Marketing'),
    (2, 'Jane Smith', 'Supervisor', 'HR'),
    (3, 'Alice Johnson', 'Developer', 'IT')
),
upsert AS (
    UPDATE employees e
    SET name = nv.name, position = nv.position, department = nv.department
    FROM new_values nv
    WHERE e.employee_id = nv.employee_id
    RETURNING e.*
)
INSERT INTO employees (employee_id, name, position, department)
SELECT employee_id, name, position, department
FROM new_values
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM upsert u
    WHERE u.employee_id = new_values.employee_id
);

WITH new_values (employee_id, name, shift_date, start_time, end_time) AS (VALUES
    (1, '2023-01-01', '08:00:00', '16:00:00'),
    (2, '2023-01-01', '09:00:00', '17:00:00'),
    (3, '2023-01-01', '10:00:00', '18:00:00')
),
upsert AS (
    UPDATE shifts s
    SET shift_date = nv.shift_date, start_time = nv.start_time, end_time = nv.end_time
    FROM new_values nv
    WHERE s.employee_id = nv.employee_id
    RETURNING s.*
)
INSERT INTO shifts (shift_id, employee_id, shift_date, start_time, end_time)
SELECT nextval('shifts_shift_id_seq'), employee_id, shift_date, start_time, end_time
FROM new_values
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM upsert u
    WHERE u.employee_id = new_values.employee_id
);
